criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  • presence of moderate to severe dementia, assessed with Global Deterioration Scale
             (GDS 4-7);

               -  presence of at least one behavioral and psychiatric symptom (BPSD) in addition to
                  depression or apathy (Lai, 2014) assessed with the NPI-NH;

               -  female gender;

               -  admission in the nursing home at least 3 months before;

               -  no previous Doll Therapy exposure;

               -  presence of a daughter or a son, as a family caregiver

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  male gender

          -  presence of previous comorbid mental disorders, such as major depression, bipolar
             disorders and schizophrenia;

          -  inability to sit comfortably on a chair or limitations in mobility of the arms;

          -  presence of acute clinical conditions interfering with the participation to the study
